The paper deals with video action recognition, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a neural network to encode spatiotemporal and motion features, which is a task that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also introduces a new block architecture, which could be considered a contribution to multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
